ringer
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the shearer with the highest tally in a gang, or a shearing-shed; the fastest shearer in a shearing gang, who usually shears on the stand closest to the wool table
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
