Quote:  `Ringer,' of course, persists for the fastest hand in a shed; with about an equal probability of derivation from the man, horse, or ship that runs `rings' round an antagonist, or from the ringer of the bell that has marked success in many games or contests besides that of the sportive `shooting gallery.'
